any unfavorable symptoms, signs, or disease temporally associated with the use of a medical

ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: Something distinguishable as an identifiable class based on common qualities.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Events associated with an electrically powered device where an electrical malfunction results in a device problem (e.g. electrical circuitry, contact or component failed) even if the problem is intermittent.

Concepts.definition: Events associated with an electrically powered device where an electrical malfunction results in a device problem (e.g. electrical circuitry, contact or component failed) even if the problem is intermittent.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Problems relating to, caused by or affecting biological processes or living organisms.

Concepts.definition: Problems relating to, caused by or affecting biological processes or living organisms.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Problems related to the device software.

Concepts.definition: Problems related to the device software.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Problems related to the optical properties of a device.

Concepts.definition: Problems related to the optical properties of a device.

PermissibleValues.value: Device End of Life Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device End of Life Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device End of Life Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems that occur from its reaching the end of its useful life.

Concepts.definition: Problems traced to the device reaching the end of its useful life.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device malfunction or problem that occurs because the device was not properly maintained according to the instructions (e.g., maintenance may be performed by user facility, distributor, or service provider).

Concepts.definition: A device malfunction or problem that occurs after production because the device was not properly maintained according to the instructions (e.g. maintenance may be performed by user facility, distributor, or service provider).

PermissibleValues.value: Device Dust or Dirt Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Dust or Dirt Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Dust or Dirt Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that experienced problems due to dust or dirt that has adhered to its surfaces.

Concepts.definition: A device that experienced problems due to ingress, or coating, of dust or dirt.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that has inadequate or incorrect insulation material.

Concepts.definition: Problems due to inadequate or incorrect electrical insulation material.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device or a component of a device that has moved from its original location due to external forces (e.g. stent or lead movement).

Concepts.definition: A device that has moved from its original location due to external forces (e.g. stent or lead movement).

PermissibleValues.value: Device Gradient Induced Field Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Gradient Induced Field Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Gradient Induced Field Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems that result from the gradient induced fields generated during radiologic procedures e.g. magnetic resonance imaging.

Concepts.definition: Problems that result from the gradient-induced fields generated during radiologic procedures e.g. magnetic resonance imaging.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Manufacturing Process Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Manufacturing Process Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Manufacturing Process Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Problems with a device that can be traced back to a problem in the manufacturing and/or production process.

Concepts.definition: Problems with a device that can be traced to a problem in the manufacturing and/or production process.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device affects the ability of the blood to clot which may be induced by chemical, mechanical, or thermal properties of the device.

Concepts.definition: The device affects the ability of the blood to clot which may be induced by chemical, mechanical, or thermal properties of the device.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Hardware Timing Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Hardware Timing Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Hardware Timing Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A problem that results from improper sequencing or activation of electronic components.

Concepts.definition: Problems that results from improper sequential activation of components.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device software contained software errors that did not impact its operation.

Concepts.definition: The device software contained software errors that did not impact its operation.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device affects or impacts the blood or its components. (See ISO 10993)

Concepts.definition: The device affects or impacts the blood or its components. (See ISO 10993 all parts)

PermissibleValues.value: Device Chemical Agent Damage Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Chemical Agent Damage Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Chemical Agent Damage Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that experienced damage as the result of a chemical agent used during the sterilization process e.g. excessive residual chemical or an incompatible sterilant.

Concepts.longName: Device Chemical Agent Damage Evaluation Result
Concepts.definition: A device that experienced damage as the result of a chemical agent used during the sterilization process e.g. excessive residual chemical or an incompatible sterilant.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Material or Material Leachate Pyrogenic Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Material or Material Leachate Pyrogenic Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Material or Material Leachate Pyrogenic Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The undesirable presence of pyrogens or fever-producing organisms caused by materials that permeate through the device.

Concepts.longName: Material or Material Leachate Pyrogenic Problem
Concepts.definition: The undesirable presence of pyrogens or fever-producing organisms caused by materials that permeate through the device.

PermissibleValues.value: Device No Results Available Since No Evaluation Performed Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device No Results Available Since No Evaluation Performed Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device No Results Available Since No Evaluation Performed Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: For use when no methods were performed and therefore no results will be obtained.

Concepts.definition: Use when no investigation can be performed and therefore no results will be obtained.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device's ability to cause damage to genetic material (e.g., leading malignant tumors). (See ISO 10993)

Concepts.definition: The device's ability to cause damage to genetic material (e.g. leading to malignant tumors).

PermissibleValues.value: Device Cleaning Disinfecting Sterilization Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Cleaning Disinfecting Sterilization Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Cleaning Disinfecting Sterilization Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device problem that occurred during or as the result of the cleaning, disinfecting, or sterilizing process.

Concepts.longName: Device Cleaning Disinfecting Sterilization Problem Evaluation Result
Concepts.definition: A device problem that occurred during or as the result of the cleaning, disinfecting, or sterilizing process.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device or component had faulty (incomplete or incorrect) software design.

Concepts.definition: The device had faulty (incomplete or incorrect) software design.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Foreign Material Contamination Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Foreign Material Contamination Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Foreign Material Contamination Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The undesirable presence of any substance that does not belong either on the device or in an organism and may lead to infection or fever.

Concepts.definition: The undesirable presence of living organisms such as bacteria, fungi, or viruses or their products (enzymes or toxins).

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that malfunctions due to a component(s) that does not operate correctly and according to the device's specifications.

Concepts.definition: A device that malfunctions due to a component(s)/accessory that does not operate correctly and according to the device's specifications.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems that occur when the device becomes worn, weakened, corroded, or broken down due to processes such as aging, permeation, and corrosion.

Concepts.definition: Problems that occur when the device becomes worn, weakened, corroded, or broken down due to processes such as aging, permeation, and corrosion.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Materials and Chemistry Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Materials and Chemistry Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Materials and Chemistry Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device malfunctions that arise from problems with its components or materials or how its materials or components react to other elements either within the device or within the environment.

Concepts.definition: Problems with the device materials or how its materials react to other elements either within the device or within the environment.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Failure to Calibrate Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Failure to Calibrate Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Failure to Calibrate Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that cannot calibrate (establish the relationship between a measuring device and the units of measure) to ensure accurate readings.

Concepts.longName: Failure to Calibrate or Used Out of Calibration
Concepts.definition: A device that cannot calibrate (establish the relationship between a measuring device and the units of measure) or is used out of calibration to ensure accurate readings.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems that result from internal or external forces including fluids, other objects, or environmental or physiologic influences.

Concepts.definition: Problems that result from internal or external forces including fluids, other objects, or environmental or physiologic influences.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Non-Terminating Software Code Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Non-Terminating Software Code Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Non-Terminating Software Code Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device software failed to provide a safe exit from a repeating code segment.

Concepts.longName: Device Non-Terminating Software Code Evaluation Result
Concepts.definition: The device software failed to provide a safe exit from a repeating code segment.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device's ability to change genetic information (usually DNA) of an organism and thus increasing the frequency of mutations.

Concepts.definition: The device's ability to change genetic information (usually DNA) of an organism and thus increasing the frequency of mutations.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems caused by the separation of a component, object, or material into two or more pieces including shear.

Concepts.definition: Problems caused by the separation of a component, object, or material into two or more pieces including shear.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that experienced problems due to sudden and momentary bursts of electrical current flowing between 2 objects at different electrical potentials.

Concepts.definition: Problems due to sudden and momentary bursts of electrical current flowing between two objects at different electrical potentials.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device causes cellular or tissue responses that elicit an undesirable local or systemic effect in the recipient or beneficiary of that therapy (see ISO 10993).

Concepts.definition: The device causes cellular or tissue responses that elicit an undesirable local or systemic effect in the recipient or beneficiary of that therapy. (See ISO 10993)

PermissibleValues.value: Device Mechanical Shock Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Mechanical Shock Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Mechanical Shock Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems caused by the sudden violent blow or collision to the whole device (e.g. by dropping).

Concepts.definition: Problems caused by the sudden violent blow or collision to the whole device (e.g. by dropping).

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device interferes with an organism's ability to clear pathogens which may be caused by an interaction with chemicals or materials.

Concepts.definition: The device affects the body's ability to activate the complement system of the immune system, thereby interfering with the ability to clear pathogens. This may be caused by an interaction of the device with chemicals or materials.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device problem that occurred because of the presence of either too much or too little lubricant where required (e.g., connectors, leading to failure mechanisms such as corrosion).

Concepts.definition: Problems that occurred because of the presence of either too much or too little lubricant where required (e.g. connectors, leading to failure mechanisms such as corrosion).

PermissibleValues.value: Device Loss of Power Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Loss of Power Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Loss of Power Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that experienced problems due to a loss in the power supply.

Concepts.definition: A device that experienced problems due to a loss in the power supply.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Devices that do not send or receive adequate signals (this speaks to the interoperability between devices).

Concepts.definition: Devices that do not send or receive adequate signals (this speaks to the interoperability between devices).

PermissibleValues.value: Device Interface Design Error Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Interface Design Error Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Interface Design Error Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device software was found to contain errors in the user interface (including usability problems) or the interfaces with other systems.

Concepts.definition: The device software was found to contain errors in the user interface (including usability problems) or the interfaces with other systems.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Software Timing Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Software Timing Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Software Timing Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device problem that results from the incorrect sequencing or activation of software modules.

Concepts.definition: Problems that results from the incorrect sequencing or activation of software modules.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device problem related to how the materials react inappropriately (e.g. over-react or under-react).

Concepts.definition: Problems that occur due to the reactivity of materials (e.g. over-react or under-react).

PermissibleValues.value: Device Software Installation Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Software Installation Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Software Installation Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device software was not installed as per the specifications or failed to properly install.

Concepts.definition: The device software was not installed as per the specifications or failed to properly install.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Problems with a device due the loss or weakening of a signal or signals.

Concepts.definition: Problems due to the loss or weakening of an electrical signal or signals.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Runtime Memory Access Error Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Runtime Memory Access Error Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Runtime Memory Access Error Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device software attempted to access an illegal or corrupted memory location.

Concepts.longName: Device Runtime Memory Access Error Evaluation Result
Concepts.definition: The device software attempted to access an illegal or corrupted memory location.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Problems that occur with devices used for radiographic or imaging procedures e.g. CT scanners, magnetic resonance imaging, etc.

Concepts.definition: Problems that occur with devices used for radiographic or imaging procedures e.g. CT scanners, magnetic resonance imaging.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device experiencing problems due to an unintentionally low-resistance connection between two points in an electric circuit, resulting in either excessive current flow that often causes damage or in a new shorter circuit that draws current away from the original pathways and components.

Concepts.definition: Problems due to an unintentionally low-resistance connection between two points in an electric circuit, resulting in either excessive current flow that often causes damage or in a new shorter circuit that draws current away from the original pathways and components.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Power Source Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Power Source Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Power Source Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Problems that are related to the device that provides power.

Concepts.definition: Problems related to the source that provides electrical power to the device.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Out of Bounds Error Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Out of Bounds Error Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Out of Bounds Error Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device software attempted to write data outside the allowed memory location.

Concepts.longName: Device Out of Bounds Error Evaluation Result
Concepts.definition: The device software attempted to write data outside the allowed memory location.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems related to the temperature of the component, device or use environment.

Concepts.definition: Problems related to the temperature of the device.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Optical Transmission Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Optical Transmission Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Optical Transmission Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A problem with the device's ability to pass light energy.

Concepts.definition: Problems with the device's ability to pass light energy.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Quality Control Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Quality Control Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Quality Control Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems that result from the failure to maintain or establish techniques for controlling and verifying the product specifications identified by the manufacturer.

Concepts.definition: Problems traced to the failure to maintain or establish techniques for controlling and verifying the product specifications (including materials used) identified by the manufacturer himself.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Thrombosis Activation Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Thrombosis Activation Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Thrombosis Activation Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device or component caused the formation of a stationary blood clot along the walls of a blood vessel resulting in an obstruction. The obstruction can occur by several means e.g. blood clotting problems (coagulation), clots from other areas of the body (emboli), or caused by device materials or reactions to drugs or the removal of drugs.

Concepts.definition: The device causes the formation of blood clots in or along blood vessels resulting in disturbed or disrupted blood flow.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device or component failed due to fluctuations within the power supply (e.g. transient power, power spike, power dip, or power sequencing).

Concepts.definition: The device failed due to fluctuations within the power supply (e.g. transient power, power spike, power dip, or power sequencing).

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device software contained code that could never be executed under any circumstance.

Concepts.definition: The device software contained code that could never be executed under any circumstance.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems that result from storing the device in an uncontrolled or improper environment (e.g., moisture sensitive devices stored in a humid environment).

Concepts.definition: Problems that result from storing the device in an uncontrolled or improper environment (e.g. moisture sensitive devices stored in a humid environment).

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device with an electrical circuit that does not conduct current because a switch is open, a wire is broken, etc.

Concepts.definition: Problem due to an electrical circuit that does not conduct current because a switch is open, a wire is broken, etc.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device problem that occurred when its material is either too flexible/pliable or inflexible/rigid when in contact by an applied force.

Concepts.definition: Problems that occurred when its material is either too flexible/pliable or inflexible/rigid when in contact by an applied force.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems that occur during the performance, use, or functioning of the device.

Concepts.definition: Problems that occur during the performance, use, or functioning of the device.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Unhandled Interrupt or Exception Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Unhandled Interrupt or Exception Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Unhandled Interrupt or Exception Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device software did not correctly address abnormal execution of the code.

Concepts.longName: Device Unhandled Interrupt or Exception Evaluation Result
Concepts.definition: The device software did not correctly address abnormal execution of the code.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Reproductive Toxicity Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Reproductive Toxicity Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Reproductive Toxicity Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device or component affects reproductive function, embryo development (teratogenicity), and prenatal and early postnatal development. (ISO 10993 part 3)

Concepts.definition: The device affects reproductive function, embryo development (teratogenicity), and prenatal and early postnatal development. (ISO 10993 part 3)

PermissibleValues.value: Device Software Requirement Error Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Software Requirement Error Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Software Requirement Error Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The software requirements for the device are either incomplete, inadequate, or in conflict.

Concepts.definition: The software requirements for the device are either incomplete, inadequate, or in conflict.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems caused by the constant rhythmic motion of the device, a device's component, or something in the environment to which the device is exposed.

Concepts.definition: Problems that result from a combination of specification variances of the components.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device software locked up because two or more processes were waiting for each other to finish.

Concepts.definition: The device software locked up because two or more processes were waiting for each other to finish.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Radiofrequency Induced Overheating Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Radiofrequency Induced Overheating Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Radiofrequency Induced Overheating Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An unacceptable or unexpected RF-induced temperature rise in the vicinity of a medical device or body part (usually caused by a closed current loop).

Concepts.definition: Problems due to unintended radiofrequency-induced temperature increase that can occur in the vicinity of the device.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems traced back to how the device was shipped (some examples may include the temperature of the shipping compartment or the method of transportation).

Concepts.definition: Problems traced to how the device was transported e.g. temperature of shipping compartment or method of transportation.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that experienced problems due to radiofrequency interference. RFI is a disturbance that affects an electrical circuit due to either electromagnetic conduction or electromagnetic radiation emitted from an external source.

Concepts.definition: Problems due to radiofrequency interference. RFI is a disturbance that affects an electrical circuit due to either electromagnetic conduction or electromagnetic radiation emitted from an external source.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Software Security Vulnerability Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Software Security Vulnerability Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Software Security Vulnerability Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device software failed to provide adequate authorization, access control, and accountability features.

Concepts.definition: The device software failed to provide adequate authorization, access control, protection and accountability features.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Protective System Failure Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Protective System Failure Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Protective System Failure Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that fails when the system designed to ensure its safe operation fails.

Concepts.definition: Problems related to the system(s) designed to prevent or warn about unsafe operation of the device.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Shelf Life Exceeded Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Shelf Life Exceeded Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Shelf Life Exceeded Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that has exceeded the period of time recommended by the manufacturer for storing the device without a degradation in quality.

Concepts.definition: A device that has exceeded the period of time/date recommended by the manufacturer for storing the device without a degradation in quality.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Software Runtime Error Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Software Runtime Error Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Software Runtime Error Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device software failed during operation as a result of a coding error.

Concepts.definition: The device software failed during operation as a result of a coding error.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Packaging Compromised Evaluation Result Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Packaging Compromised Evaluation Result Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Packaging Compromised Evaluation Result Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device packaging that has been opened purposefully or inadvertently thus exposing the device to the outside environment and rendering it unsterile or unclean (e.g. a broken seal or ripped or torn packaging).

Concepts.definition: Problems that occurred because of a compromised packaging of the device (e.g. broken or incomplete seal).

PermissibleValues.value: Device Platelet Activation Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Platelet Activation Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Platelet Activation Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that affects the body's ability to activate platelets which are essential to stop bleeding and repair the tissue. Platelets also play a key role in the development of acute coronary syndromes and contribute to cerebrovascular events.

Concepts.definition: The device affects the body's ability to activate platelet formation.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Reports related to the outer, protective wrapping of a device (e.g. a broken seal or ripping (compromised), lack of correct contents).

Concepts.definition: Problems that occurred because of the device packaging.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems that result from a combination of specification variances of the components.

Concepts.definition: Problems that result from a combination of specification variances of the components.

PermissibleValues.value: Incorrect Device Data Definition Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Incorrect Device Data Definition Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Incorrect Device Data Definition Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device software was found to contain errors in specifying or manipulating data items.

Concepts.definition: The device software was found to contain errors in specifying or manipulating data items.

PermissibleValues.value: Incorrect Device Software Algorithm Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Incorrect Device Software Algorithm Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Incorrect Device Software Algorithm Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device software was found to implement an incorrect sequence of steps for a specific computation.

Concepts.definition: The device software was found to implement an incorrect sequence of steps for a specific computation.

PermissibleValues.value: Improper Device Physical Structure Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Improper Device Physical Structure Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Improper Device Physical Structure Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device problem related to the incorrect or inadequate arrangement of the parts, components, elements, or materials.

Concepts.definition: Problems related to the incorrect or inadequate arrangement of the parts, components, elements, or materials.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that malfunctions as the result of exposure to the temperatures that are outside of those in the device's specifications.

Concepts.definition: Device performance was affected by the temperature, or changes in temperature, of the environment in which it was used.

PermissibleValues.value: Inadequate Device Immunity Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Inadequate Device Immunity Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Inadequate Device Immunity Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that lacks adequate immunity or capabilities to resist electromagnetic interference (EMI).

Concepts.definition: Problems related to immunity or capabilities to resist electromagnetic interference (EMI).

PermissibleValues.value: Inappropriate or Insufficient Device Sterilization Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Inappropriate or Insufficient Device Sterilization Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Inappropriate or Insufficient Device Sterilization Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Inadequate sterilization of a device possibly resulting in the presence of microorganisms or other contaminants on the device.

Concepts.longName: Inappropriate or Insufficient Device Sterilization Evaluation Result
Concepts.definition: Inadequate sterilization of a device possibly resulting in the presence of microorganisms or other contaminants on the device.

PermissibleValues.value: Inadequate Device Labeling Content Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Inadequate Device Labeling Content Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Inadequate Device Labeling Content Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Invalid, incorrect, or inappropriate information on the labels (not including instructions for use) e.g. mislabeled contents or device labeling characteristics or package contents.

Concepts.longName: Incorrect Labeling and/or Instructions for Use
Concepts.definition: Missing, incorrect, or inappropriate information on the labels e.g. mislabeled contents or device labeling characteristics or package contents

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems related to materials that can co-exist simultaneously as part of the device.

Concepts.definition: Problems that occur due to the incompatibility of materials that co-exist simultaneously as part of the device.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device that was returned was not complete and/or is missing parts or components.

Concepts.definition: The device that was returned was not complete and/or is missing parts or components.

PermissibleValues.value: Inadequate Instructions for Device Use Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Inadequate Instructions for Device Use Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Inadequate Instructions for Device Use Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Insufficient information on the labels or in the manuals related to a device's instructions for use e.g. steps that are difficult to follow or that are missing.

Concepts.longName: Inadequate Labeling and/or Instructions for Use
Concepts.definition: Inadequate information on the labels or in the instructions for use e.g. steps that are difficult to follow or that are missing.

PermissibleValues.value: Results Pending Completion of Device Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Results Pending Completion of Device Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Results Pending Completion of Device Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: For use when the evaluation is still in progress.

Concepts.definition: Investigation is ongoing and results are not yet available. Do not use this code if the investigation is complete.

PermissibleValues.value: Reused Device not Cleaned Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Reused Device not Cleaned Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Reused Device not Cleaned Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that has been used more than once without being cleaned according to the device's cleaning instructions.

Concepts.longName: Reused Device not Cleaned Evaluation Result
Concepts.definition: A device that has been used more than once without being cleaned according to the device's cleaning instructions.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: No Value Exists

Concepts.definition: No Value Exists

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device problem caused by its surface coming in contact with another surface or fluid.

Concepts.definition: Problems caused by its surface coming in contact with another surface or fluid.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device problem that occurred due to factors within the environment e.g. dust, dirt, humidity, temperature.

Concepts.definition: Problems that occurred due to factors within the environment e.g. dust, dirt, humidity, temperature.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Improper Material Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Improper Material Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Improper Material Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems that occur due to the presence of a material that should not be present or part of the device.

Concepts.definition: Problems that occur due to the presence of a material that should not be present or part of the device.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that experienced electromagnetic interference (EMI) by physical contact with conductors (e.g. wires, resistors, terminals) as opposed to radiated EMI which is caused by induction (without physical contact of the conductors).

Concepts.definition: Problems related to electromagnetic interference (EMI) by physical contact with conductors (e.g. wires, resistors, terminals) as opposed to radiated EMI which is caused by induction (without physical contact of the conductors).

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device software performed an incorrect arithmetic operation.

Concepts.definition: The device software performed an incorrect arithmetic operation.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The undesirable presence of toxins associated with certain bacteria (e.g. gram negative bacteria).

Concepts.definition: The undesirable presence of toxins associated with certain bacteria (e.g. gram negative bacteria).

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device's ability to promote cancer or facilitate its propagation.

Concepts.definition: The device's ability to trigger development of cancer.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems associated with the improper combination of materials or elements present in the device (e.g., improper composition of the materials of a capacitor).

Concepts.definition: Problems associated with the improper combination of materials or elements present in the device (e.g. improper composition of the materials of a capacitor).

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device problem that occurred because the device was assembled or put together incorrectly.

Concepts.definition: Problems that occurred because the device was assembled incorrectly.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Energy Storage System Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Energy Storage System Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Energy Storage System Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems related to the energy storage system (e.g. the rechargeable battery, charging system, or capacitor) and includes problems such as premature power source depletion and battery explosions. An accumulator is an apparatus by means of which energy can be stored, such as a rechargeable battery or a hydraulic accumulator. Such devices may be electrical, fluidic or mechanical and are sometimes used to convert a small continuous power source into a short surge of energy or vice versa. Other examples of accumulators include capacitors, compulsators, steam accumulator, wave energy machines, pumped-storage hydroelectric plants.

Concepts.definition: Problems related to the energy storage system (e.g. the rechargeable battery, charging system, or capacitor) and includes problems such as premature power source depletion and battery explosions.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems due to incorrect version or change control.

Concepts.definition: Problems due to change control or incorrect version, including regional requirements.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Insufficient, inadequate, or incorrect information provided on a device's label or documentation regarding e.g. as the intended use, directions for use, and characteristics of the device.

Concepts.definition: Insufficient, inadequate, or incorrect information provided on a device's label or documentation regarding e.g. its intended use, directions for use, and characteristics of the device, including its maintenance.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Electromagnetic Compatibility Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Electromagnetic Compatibility Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Electromagnetic Compatibility Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device-to-device or device-environment problem resulting from electromagnetic disturbances

Concepts.definition: Device-to-device or device-environment problem resulting from electromagnetic disturbances.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The unacceptable distortion of an image due to signal loss that may occur during a radiologic procedure such as magnetic resonance imaging.

Concepts.definition: The unacceptable distortion of an image due to signal loss that may occur during a radiologic procedure such as magnetic resonance imaging.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems caused by changes in the shape or size of the device or device component due to an applied force. This can be a result of tensile forces, compressive forces, shear, bending, tensile (pulling), or torsion.

Concepts.definition: Problems caused by changes in the shape or size of the device due to an applied force. This can be a result of tensile forces, compressive forces, shear, bending, tensile (pulling), or torsion.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that malfunctions as the result of exposure to undesirable levels of humidity

Concepts.definition: Device performance was affected by the humidity, or changes in humidity, of the environment in which it was used.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems due to the weakening or breakdown of its material when subjected to stress or a series of repeated stresses.

Concepts.definition: Problems due to the weakening or breakdown of its material when subjected to stress or a series of repeated stresses.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that experienced problems due to insufficient or excessive resistance to AC current flow either by the device or circuit.

Concepts.definition: Problems due to insufficient or excessive resistance to current flow either by the device or circuit.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Data Compression Error Evaluation Result

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Magnetically Induced Torque Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Problems due to excessive torque created by the application of magnetic fields.

PermissibleValues.value: Device No Failure Detected Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device No Failure Detected Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device No Failure Detected Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device either functioned as designed or a failure was not found.

Concepts.definition: The device either functioned as intended or a problem was not found.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that malfunctions because it was incorrectly installed, set-up, or configured (e.g., misconfiguration of an automatic defibrillator to semi-automatic leading to failure)

Concepts.definition: A device that malfunctions because it was incorrectly installed, set-up, or configured (e.g. misconfiguration of an "automatic" defibrillator to "semi-automatic", thereby leading to failure).

PermissibleValues.value: Device Electrical Current Leakage Problem Evaluation Result
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Electrical Current Leakage Problem Evaluation Result

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Electrical Current Leakage Problem Evaluation Result
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that experiences problems related to small currents which may cause electric shock. Leakage current is the current that flows through the protective ground conductor to ground. In the absence of a grounding connection, it is the current that could flow from any conductive part or the surface of non-conductive parts to ground if a conductive path was available (such as a human body). There are always extraneous currents flowing in the safety ground conductor.

Concepts.definition: Problems related to leakage currents which may cause electric shock. These currents usually flow through the protective ground conductor. In its absence, these currents could flow from the device to the ground via the human body.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A problem with the mechanical, electrical, or communication interface between two or more separate devices or components.

Concepts.definition: Problems with the mechanical, electrical, or communication interface between two or more separate devices.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The undesirable presence of microorganisms or microbes such as bacteria and fungi (yeasts and molds).

Concepts.definition: The undesirable presence of microorganisms or microbes such as bacteria and fungi (yeasts and molds).

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems due to the premature or expected erosion of its material by use, deterioration, or change.

Concepts.definition: Problems due to the premature or expected erosion of its material by use, deterioration, or change.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device software assigned one type of value into a variable of another type.

Concepts.definition: The device software assigned one type of value into a variable of another type.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems caused by either excessive or inadequate physical force exerted on it by another object resulting in problems e.g. wear, bending, deformation, fracture, fatigue.

Concepts.definition: Problems caused by either excessive or inadequate physical force exerted on it by another object resulting in problems e.g. wear, bending, deformation, fracture, fatigue.
